The paper deals with cognitive radio systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The use of multiple antennas and beamforming techniques is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) communities. Finally, the paper deals with interference constraints and protection of primary users, which are important topics in the area of communications and networking security (cs.CR).
